Sealing Sean S.'s ratings system: Scale of 1-10 (single visit): Food   8 *Drinks*   not rated Service   8 Atmosphere   8 Value  7  I'd heard good things about Rustler's Rooste, so when my mother came to visit over the holidays, it was the perfect excuse to go.  The view at night is fantastic and the restaurant itself definitely has a kitsch factor you don't find any more.  We were seated without a wait, drinks, bread, and meals were delivered promptly, and our server checked in on us enough times so we didn't feel ignored, but she wasn't intrusive.  The cotton candy at the end was a fun surprise.  My one nit pick is that the tables seem to be really undersized, and very close together.  So there literally wasn't enough room for main dishes, sides, the bread and our drinks, and we kept getting bumped into by people at the other tables as well as people walking by.  Maybe it was just a slow night, but it looked like they had plenty of room to take out a few tables, and make the remaining tables a bit bigger and space them a bit further apart.  Overall, I'd go again, and I'd recommend taking friends and family from out of town there for dinner with a view.

