Chase Field is a great venue to catch a baseball game.  It's very walkable.  Compared to Chicago, parking is cheap, and the concessions are very reasonable.  Best of all you can actually afford to buy tickets.  In other words, you can afford to take your family to a baseball game without spending the equivalent of a month's rent in the process.  It's clean, modern, and well-lit.  It's great with the roof open or closed.  And you can hang out in a freaking pool and watch a baseball game!  Plenty of concession stands and bathrooms mean you won't be wandering aimlessly.  After several visits, I can honestly say I've never not had a good time.

